      "amount": "3 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "grand marnier liqueur",
      "amount": "1 tablespoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "salt",
      "amount": "to taste"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 200°C (400°F).",
    "Mix almond flour, ground almonds, eggs, soy sauce, vinegar, sesame oil, chili flakes, ginger paste, water, and salt in a bowl until combined.",
    "Transfer the mixture into a greased dish and bake for about 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "While baking, heat a pan with sesame oil over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the batter from the oven to the pan and stir-fry for an additional 3-4 minutes.",
    "Drizzle grand marnier on top before serving as a post-workout snack.",
    "Serve immediately."
  ],
